extends KMedoids
implements weka.core.TechnicalInformationHandler

Cluster data using the kMedoids algorithm with a modification in the medoid to consider feature-class correlation.See:

Thiago F. Covões, Eduardo R. Hruschka (2011). Towards Improving Cluster-Based Feature Selection with a Simplified Silhouette Filter. Information Sciences. 181(18):3766-3782.

BibTeX: 

 @article{Covões2011,
    author = {Thiago F. Covões and Eduardo R. Hruschka},
    journal = {Information Sciences},
    number = {18},
    pages = {3766-3782},
    title = {Towards Improving Cluster-Based Feature Selection with a Simplified Silhouette Filter},
    volume = {181},
    year = {2011},
    ISSN = {0020-0255}
 }

Valid options are: 

 -N <num>
  number of clusters.
  (default 2).
 -A <classname and options>
  Distance function to use.
 
 -I <num>
  Maximum number of iterations.
 
 -O
  Preserve order of instances.
